— Synthetic data (models trained partly on data generated by other models — this works surprisingly well and is now standard)

— Reinforcement learning from human/AI feedback (the "alignment" layer, but it doubles as a training signal)

— Multimodal expansion (video, audio, code, scientific data — much less explored than text)

— Better data efficiency (smaller models trained better, like Phi-4 doing 70B-level work at 14B)

— Permissioned high-quality corpora (publishers, scientific archives, code repositories with licenses)
